<HEADLINE> UK Summons Yemeni Ambassador over Hostages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Yemen's ambassador to London was
summoned on Friday to the British Foreign Office for the second
time in two days for talks on the battle in Yemen in which three
Britons died.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Hussein al-Amri was told again of British
dissatisfaction over the incident.
</P>
<P>
Britain wanted to make clear of exactly what happened on
Tuesday. Officials said earlier that the government would be very
concerned if it turned out that its advice to seek a negotiated
solution to the kidnap saga was ignored.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Office Minister Joyce Quin summoned the Ambassador for
New Year's Day talks.
</P>
<P>
"This is to reinforce what we have already said. We attach
great importance to establishing what actually happened," a
Foreign Office official said.
</P>
<P>
"We want to clarify the discrepancies from the different
stories that have come from the hostages and the Yemeni
authorities," she added.
</P>
<P>
The four hostages were killled and two wounded on Tuesday when
Yemeni security forces raided a hideout where kidnappers were
holding a party of foreign tourists.
</P>
<P>
Yemen's interior ministry has said that there had been no time
for negotiations as the kidnappers had started killing hostages.
</P>
</TEXT>
