<HEADLINE> Blast Destroys 2 Cars in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 1 (Xinhua) -- A man was slightly injured and
two vehicles were destroyed Friday when a bomb exploded near a popular
tourist destination in Cape Town, South African Press Association
(SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
It was believed that the bomb was placed in or under a car at a
parking area near the Victoria and Alfred Waterfront, SAPA quoted a
police spokesperson as saying.
</P>
<P>
Details were not available at this stage.
</P>
<P>
The waterfront was the scene of a bomb blast in August 1998 when
two people were killed and 26 others injured in a pipe bomb
explosion at the American-franchised Planet Hollywood restaurant.
</P>
</TEXT>
