<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Kupang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.9 on
the Richter scale jolted Kupang, East Nusatenggara province of
Indonesia, at about 12:27 local time on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the tremor was 33 kilometers in the depth of
the sea, some 58 kilometers southeast of Kupang, Antara News
Agency quoted head of the Kupang Geophysics office Ibnu Purwana as
saying.
</P>
<P>
"The quake was felt by many people both in and outside of
houses," Purwana said, adding that the tremor however had caused
neither material damage nor human casualty.  
