<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Trade with European Countries in Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Special Functions
Minister Daim Zainuddin said Saturday night that the country would
trade with the European countries in the Euro in future as an
alternative to using the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The government is prepared to use the Euro in line with efforts
to reduce the use of the dollar in trade, he said in Sungai
Petani, northern state of Kedah, according to the Malaysian
national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
"We should reduce the use of the dollar because our trade with
the United States makes up only 18 percent of our total trade, but
70 percent of our dealings with other countries is conducted in
the dollar," he was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Daim said the use of the Euro was a good sign because it would
pose competition to the greenback.
</P>
<P>
The members of the European Union started using the Euro as a
single currency in all their trading Friday. 
