<DOCNO> XIE19990102.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wachter Captures World Cup Giant Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Austrian veteran Anita Wachter
skied superbly to win her second title of the week by taking the
women's World Cup giant slalom race in Maribor of Slovenia on
Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Wachter, 31, clocked two minutes 15.66 seconds to head Sonia
Nef of Switzerland by 0.91 seconds after the two legs. Overall
World Cup leader Alexandra Meissnitzer of Austria was third, 0.99
behind.
</P>
<P>
It was Wachter's second giant slalom win in a row. She also
won at Semmering, Austria, on December 27.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Saturday, Hilde Gerg edged out fellow German Martina
Ertl to win a women's Super-G race.
</P>
<P>
Olympic slalom champion Gerg, who won a downhill event at
Veysonnaz, Switzerland, a week before Christmas, clocked 1:30.17
seconds to finish 0.13 seconds in front of Ertl.
</P>
<P>
Michaela Dorfmeister of Austria was third at 0:29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
