<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan Inspector-General of Police Cossy
Odomel has said that he will resign soon from the top police post and live
a normal civilian life, Radio Uganda reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He made the shocking remarks at an annual party hosted for senior police
officers at Mamboole Sports Hotel here Friday, said the radio.
</P>
<P>
Presidential Press Secretary Hope Kivengere told Xinhua Saturday that
she does not know the matter and does now know whether President Yoweri
Museveni has received Odomel's resignation.
</P>
