<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Wins Spot in Hopman Cup Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- France posted an emphatic win
over Zimbabwe Saturday to snare the eighth and final spot in the
Hopman Cup in Perth, a coastal city in west Australia.
</P>
<P>
The French team of Guillaume Raoux and Sandrine Testud won the
qualifying tie against the Black siblings, Cara and Wayne, to
claim its place in Group A of the mixed teams tournament.
</P>
<P>
Under the Hopman Cup format, each tie consists of a men's
singles and women's singles rubber, as well as a mixed doubles
encounter.
</P>
<P>
After Testud had won the first match of the tie in three sets,
Raoux sealed the result with a straight sets win in the men's
singles.
</P>
<P>
The Blacks gained some consolation with a straight sets win in
the doubles.
</P>
<P>
France was runner-up at last year's Hopman Cup, when
represented by Mary Pierce and Cedric Pioline.
</P>
<P>
Raoux, ranked 55th in the world, was always in control against
Black and took the first set in quick time, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Black, ranked 97, showed renewed fight in the second set and
saved four match points before succumbing 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, Testud overcame a slow start to win in
three sets.
</P>
<P>
Cara Black, ranked 44 in the world, won the first set 6-4, but
Testud, ranked 14, dropped just three games from that point on,
winning the last two sets 6-1 6-2 to give France a one- nil lead.
</P>
<P>
France now plays tournament favorite Spain on Monday and
Testud said she and Raoux took great heart from last year's
performance of the Slovak Republic, who won the tournament after
qualifying.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow sees the tournament proper begin with Australia,
looking for its first win in the Hopman Cup, up against South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
US Open runner-up Mark Philippoussis and exciting teenager
Jelena Dokic represent the home side against perennial Hopman Cup
partners Wayne Ferreira and Amanda Coetzer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
