<DOCNO> XIE19990102.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Volkswagen Leads China's Top 500 Joint Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Volkswagen
Automotive Company Ltd. has for the 7th consecutive year led
China's top 500 overseas-invested enterprises in sales volume,
according to an annual list just released by the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The company had a sales volume of 26.3 billion yuan in the
1997-98 financial year, a year-on-year rise of 8.2 percent over
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Among the top ten are Motorola (China) Electronics Ltd.,
Yangtze Optical Fiber and Cable Company, Konka Group Co.,
Guangdong Nuclear Power Joint Venture, Shanghai Bell Telephone
Equipment Manufacturing Co., and FAW-Volkswagen Automobile Co.
</P>
<P>
The combined sales volume of the 500 overseas-invested
businesses rose 27.97 percent to 601.238 billion yuan; the average
company's sales volume stood at 1.202 billion yuan, an increase of
262 million yuan over the previous financial year.
</P>
<P>
There are 174 companies whose sales volumes surpassing one
billion yuan each; while the number of such companies a year ago
was 124.
</P>
<P>
The 500 companies' combined assets rose 41.97 percent to
697.758 billion yuan. There are 59 companies whose assets
surpassing two billion yuan each.
</P>
<P>
The 500 companies made a combined profit of 45.677 billion
yuan, an increase of 9.677 billion yuan. About 90 percent of the
companies made profits.
</P>
<P>
Among the top 500 companies, 420 are in the manufacturing
sector and had a combined sales volume of 519.927 billion
yuan. The rest of the companies are involved in such sectors as
power, gas and water production and supply, trade, catering
service, real estate, and transport.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong and Macao take the predominant position in the top
500, with 212 businesses on the mainland. The United States and
Japan have invested in 54 and 48 companies respectively in China.
</P>
<P>
About 87.6 percent of the top 500, or 438 companies, are
located in the coastal regions. And 161 of the top 500 are in
Guangdong Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
