<HEADLINE> Abducted German Tourists Leave Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Four German tourists, including
three women and a man, who were taken hostages by terrorists on
December 6, 1996, left Yemen early Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Seeing the tourists off at the airport Saturday morning, Yemeni
Undersecretary of Tourism Mutahar Ahmed Taqey regretted over their
abduction experience, the Yemeni News Agency (YNA) said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the incident would not have adverse
impact on the Yemeni-German intimate friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
German Ambassador to Yemen Helga Graefin Strachwitz told YNA
that she was glad for the release of the German tourists
after 4 weeks in capture.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador agreed with the Yemeni official that the
incident would not affect the bilateral relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
On December 30, 1998, the Yemeni security forces managed to set
free the four German tourists taken hostages by Yemeni clans in
Beni Debian area, Ma'reb province, east to the Yemeni capital of
Sanaa. 
</P>
