<HEADLINE> Vietnam's GDP Up 5.83 Percent in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's gross domestic product
(GDP ) grew by 5.83 percent in 1998, Vietnam News Agency (VNA)
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency said Vietnam obtained major
socioeconomic development achievements in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural production grew by 2.73 percent, industrial
production 10.25 percent and services 4.22 percent.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production value increased by 12.1 percent,
agricultural production value 3.6 percent and services 5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's total export turnover rose by 0.9 percent while
import value dropped by 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Its total social investment was estimated at 87 trillion
Vietnamese dong (6.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
VNA said Vietnam also saw progress in renovating production
relations, improving people's living conditions, developing
socio-cultural activities and ensuring national defense and social
security.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government targets 1999's GDP growth at between
5 and 6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
