<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0840 GMT, January 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January -- Nine people were killed and 25 injured by
an avalanche in northern Quebec of Canada early Friday, reports
said, raising the previous toll of eight.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy struck at about midnight Friday as some 400 to 500
people were packed into the school gym of an Inuit village
celebrating the New Year.
</P>
<P>
Six people died soon after the avalanche crashed into the gym,
while three other victims were discovered several hours later,
buried deep under mounds of snow, the reports said. (Canada-A
valanche-1st add)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- A moderate earthquake measuring at 5.1 degree on the
open-ended Richter scale rocked central Iran Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
