see chain stores to stop importing certain agricultural products to protect
local ones, Zambia Daily Mail newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Finance Minister Edith Nawakwi as saying that the in-
coming crops will be subjected to stringent scrutiny and surely most of
them will find it difficult to enter the country.
</P>
<P>
The minister advised major super markets to enter into agreements with
local suppliers.
</P>
<P>
