<HEADLINE> Tanzania Trade Deficit Narrows Last November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's trade deficit narrowed
to 32 million U.S. Dollars last November from 53.8 million Dollars in
the previous month, according to Tanzania's central bank.
</P>
<P>
The improvement in the trade account can be attributed to an
increase of 21 percent in exports, from 71.9 million Dollars in October to
87 million Dollars in November, the central bank said in its latest monthly
economic review.
</P>
<P>
The report said there were increases in both volume and unit
prices for traditional export crops, mainly agricultural produce.
</P>
<P>
"Except for cotton whose volume declined by 16.5 percent and
sisal whose unit price decreased by 29.3 percent, all other
traditional exports, namely coffee, tea, tobacco and cashew nut
recorded significant increases in export volumes and unit prices,"
it said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the central bank said that imports during November
decreased by 5.3 percent to 119 million Dollars from 125 million recorded
in October. 
</P>
