<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The anti-government National
Democratic Front (NDF) is building up its forces by recruiting
more fighters after suffering a series of debacles during the past
eight years.
</P>
<P>
In a report released here Saturday, the Armed Forces of the
Philippines (AFP) said the group headed by its exiled leader Jose
Ma. Sison enlisted 624 new recruits last year, increasing their
fighting force from 5,406 in 1997 to 6,030 in 1998.
</P>
