as of December 31, 1998, slightly up by 346 firearms from the 1997
figure of 4,841.
</P>
<P>
Since their disastrous defeat in the past years after the AFP
launched its counter-insurgency program, the NDF has been trying
to regain its foothold in the countryside, it said.
</P>
<P>
The AFP said anti-government activities by the NDF have
increased slightly from 174 in 1997 to 186 in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The on-going peace talks between the government and the NDF
have somewhat minimized the number of killed and wounded, the AFP
said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, it said, only 109 NDF guerrillas were killed while
government forces suffered 70 deaths, including 20 policemen.
