<HEADLINE> Philippines to Intensify Crackdown on Drug Dealers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine National Police
(PNP) will shift its operations to the fight against drug
trafficking this year following the neutralization of 15
kidnap-for-ransom syndicates in the past six months.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency Saturday quoted a PNP spokesman as
saying the police have neutralized 15 kidnap gangs since July last
year.
</P>
<P>
Among the big-time kidnap-for-ransom groups rendered
ineffective were the Sarabia group, Baleleng group and the "P50
Million" kidnap gang, he said.
</P>
<P>
The 15 kidnap-for-ransom gangs were responsible for a series of
kidnapping incidents in Metro Manila in the past years until they
were neutralized by the police.
</P>
<P>
With the neutralization of kidnapping cases, the spokesman
said, the PNP will concentrate its job in stamping out other
crimes, particularly drug trafficking, the country's number-one
problem at present.
</P>
<P>
He said that usually kidnap gangs shift their operations to
other illegal activities as their strategy of what they call "a
cool-off period" when the police are pursuing kidnap-for-ransom
syndicates relentlessly. 
</P>
