<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Olympic Association Ad Hoc Body Formed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- An ad hoc executive committee of
the Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA) was formed on Friday
with Army Chief Lt. General Mustafizur Rahman as president, it
was learnt from the National Sports Council (NSC) Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The other BOA's office bearers are Vice-Presidents Lt. Col.
(Retd.)Mohammad Faruk Khan, Brigadier kazi Hamood Hasan and Addul
Awal Mintoo, and Secretary General Zafar Imam.
</P>
<P>
The 32-member provisional body of the BOA has been formed as
per provision of the National Sports Council Act Law 1974
(amended till 1991).
</P>
<P>
Under the law, president or vice-presidents of concerned
sports federations or associations will represent them in the BOA
executive committee.
</P>
<P>
The NSC, supreme body of the country's sports, dissolved the
33-member previous ad hoc committee on December 23, 1998,
following a long time tug of war between the NSC and the BOA over
delegation of power. 
</P>
