<HEADLINE> Soeharto's Family Owns 4.3 Million Hectares of Forest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian former president
Soeharto's family controls at least 4.3 million hectares of forest
concessions in the country, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
The 4.3 million hectares of forest were owned by the Soeharto
family through their stakes in 65 timber companies, local leading
newspapers Saturday quoted Minister of Forestry and Plantations
Muslimin Nasution as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The ownership of those timber companies is in the names of
Soeharto's children, grand-children, brother and his sons-in-low
and daughter-in-low. There is no stake in either Soeharto's name
or Ibu Thien's (Soeharto's late wife) name," the minister told the
ministry's year-end media briefing on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said the estimate of the size of the forest areas controlled
by the Soeharto family was based on the percentage of their shares
in the 65 timber companies.
</P>
<P>
The family has stakes of between 10 percent and 100 percent in
the 65 companies.
</P>
<P>
Director General of Forest utilization Waskito Soerjodibroto
said earlier the ministry's investigator had discovered that 9.4
million hectares of the country's forests and plantations were
owned or controlled by former president Soeharto, his family and
close associates.
</P>
<P>
"The remaining 5.1 million hectares were controlled by
Soeharto's cronies through shares held in various companies,"
Muslimin said.
</P>
<P>
He said his ministry found a strong indication that those
properties were acquired by the Soeharto family and their cronies
through corruptive, collusive and nepotistic (KKN) practices.
</P>
