<HEADLINE> At Least Eight Killed in Avalanche in Quebec Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people, including
five young children, were killed and 25 injured Friday when an
avalanche hit a Quebec village during a New Year celebration,
police said.
</P>
<P>
Some 400 to 500 people were attending the festivities just
after midnight in a school gym in the Inuit village of
Kangiqsualujjuaq, some 1,500 kilometers north of Montreal, when
heaps of snow shattered one of the walls.
</P>
<P>
Police said the victims included five children younger than
eight and the injured included nine children. At least one boy
was still missing as the search was going on.
</P>
<P>
The injured were being taken to hospitals by planes since the
town, where some 650 residents live, has no doctors but only two
nurses.
</P>
<P>
Police said the gym was buried by snow between one and four
meters, with the roof threatening to cave in, while another
avalanche was possible. 
</P>
