<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Create World's Lightest Electromagnetic Motor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
developed a 12.5-milligram electromagnetic motor, the lightest
in the world.
</P>
<P>
Developed by the scientists in Jiaotong University in
Shanghai, the micro-motor is expected to be powerful, durable and
able to be used in medical appliances, micro-robots and for
military applications.
</P>
<P>
Using an endoscope driven by the micro-motor, doctors will have
a clearer view of the patient's anatomy, and most of the
endoscope's operations will be automatic, according to Zhang Chen,
a leading scientist in the development program.
</P>
<P>
This electromagnetic motor can also be used on non-pilot
aircraft reconnaissance flights, Zhang said. 
