through dialogue and negotiations."
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese president Jiang Zemin and US president Bill Clinton
exchanged letters with each other yesterday, both pledging to
increase mutual understanding and make greater efforts toward
building a trustworthy partnership between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
-- Beijing sounded its 600-year-old giant bell to herald in the
advent of the year 1999. The 46-ton bell is the biggest bell in
China.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Beijing Vice-Mayor Wang Guangtao led a city-wide inspection
yesterday as new auto-emission standards came into effect.
</P>
<P>
Together with officials from the Environmental Protection
Administration and the Traffic Control Office of Beijing, Wang
inspected several major intersections in the city.
</P>
<P>
Among the 124 cars randomly checked during the New Year's Day,
over 80 cars failed to meet the new standards. The drivers'
licenses were immediately confiscated and they were ordered
to improve their car emission equipment within a set period of
time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
