<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cardoso Sworn In as Brazilian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Fernando Henrique Cardoso was
sworn in as president of Brazil for another four-year term on
Friday, the first reelected president in the republic's 109-year
history.
</P>
<P>
He made a 20-minute speech after the swearing in, reaffirming
to fulfill his promises in the October election, such as a
sustained economic growth, a fairer distribution of wealth and
more jobs.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso also mentioned the importance of the South American
Common Market, of which Brazil is a member, saying that "we are
creating an integrated space of peace, democracy, and shared
prosperity in South America."
</P>
<P>
He noted that his government will strengthen relations with
the European Union, Russia, China, Japan and African countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
