<HEADLINE> Foreman-Holmes Bout Called Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The bout between George
Foreman and Larry Holmes scheduled for January 23 has been called
off, according to Foreman's brother roy Foreman.
</P>
<P>
"George says it's off," Roy Foreman said, adding that promoter
Roger Levitt did not meet the deadline for paying Foreman the
remaining 9 million dollars of his 10 million dollars purse.
</P>
<P>
"They were supposed to have the money last week and they
didn't have it," Roy Foreman said. "George gave them an extra
week and they still didn't have it."
</P>
<P>
The 12-round bout was scheduled for two weeks after Foreman's
50th birthday. Holmes, who was 49 on November 3, had promised it
would be worth the money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
