<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Stops to Tax Foreign Investors on Bond Interest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Greece begins as of Friday to
scrap a tax on bond interest for foreign investors in a move
aligning the market with remaining European Union (EU) countries.
</P>
<P>
It also scraps tax on bonds issued before 1999 but payable in
that year under the old regime, according to the semi-official
Athens News Agency (ANA).
</P>
<P>
Until now, Greece was the only country in the 15-nation EU that
taxed foreign investors on bond interest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
